<div id="review_5599877" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/5599877" />
    <a title="Katie Lynch" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/332144-katie-lynch"><img alt="Katie Lynch" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/5599877?book_show_action=true">Sep 03, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Katie Lynch" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Katie Lynch" href="/user/show/332144-katie-lynch">Katie Lynch</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">not really anyone</span></div>

        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/332144-katie-lynch?shelf=yuck">yuck</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer5599877" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17818101700208939890">Hey Roth, I know you have a great vocabulary...Just tell me a damn story. <br/><br/>Let me explain: I just read a very positive review of this book stating that Roth has such an expansive vocabulary, and every word seems painstakingly chosen, etc. That is exactly what I hate about this book! A narrative is supposed to flow, not make you resolve to study the dictionary more fastidiously. <br/><br/>For the record, I have a pretty good vocabulary and I thorouoghly enjoy creative uses of the English language. But I des</span>
  <span id="freeText17818101700208939890" style="display:none">Hey Roth, I know you have a great vocabulary...Just tell me a damn story. <br /><br />Let me explain: I just read a very positive review of this book stating that Roth has such an expansive vocabulary, and every word seems painstakingly chosen, etc. That is exactly what I hate about this book! A narrative is supposed to flow, not make you resolve to study the dictionary more fastidiously. <br /><br />For the record, I have a pretty good vocabulary and I thorouoghly enjoy creative uses of the English language. But I despise the use of overly academic, deliberately "highbrow" language when something simple would tell the story better. The problem is NOT that I didn't understand this book, it is that the plot just does not flow at all. I really dislike this book. <br /><br />It looks as though this is a pretty unpopular opinion, but oh well.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17818101700208939890" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
