<div id="review_4428376644" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4428376644" />
    <a title="Vince" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/128225739-vince"><img alt="Vince" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1629724401p2/128225739.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4428376644?book_show_action=true">Jan 04, 2022</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Vince" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Vince" href="/user/show/128225739-vince">Vince</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780375726347" href="/book/show/228381.The_Human_Stain">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4428376644" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer302471794084350541"><b>As it is a human thing to have a secret, it is also a human thing, sooner or later, to reveal itself.</b><br/><br/>What a way to start off the new year! Coleman Silk has a secret. What that is, the reader must find out. After a mistaken interpretation of a innocuous epithet, Coleman&apos;s career as a college classics professor all comes crumbling down around his ears. He&apos;s forced to retire and is ostracized by the entire University. On top of everything else, he&apos;s having a secret affair with the college janitor w</span>
  <span id="freeText302471794084350541" style="display:none"><b>As it is a human thing to have a secret, it is also a human thing, sooner or later, to reveal itself.</b><br /><br />What a way to start off the new year! Coleman Silk has a secret. What that is, the reader must find out. After a mistaken interpretation of a innocuous epithet, Coleman's career as a college classics professor all comes crumbling down around his ears. He's forced to retire and is ostracized by the entire University. On top of everything else, he's having a secret affair with the college janitor who is old enough to be his daughter. Phillip Roth writes about unhappy people and he pulls all the stops with this one. He's gone on record saying he's fascinated by unhappy people and to be honest, so am I. The prose had me enraptured from start to finish. Roth grabs you by the ears and doesn't let go. He writes with such passion, intensity and emotion and every character's story is compelling, even the minor characters. An utter masterpiece and I can't wait to read more by Philip Roth.<br /><br />5 out 5.</span>
  <a data-text-id="302471794084350541" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


